Dębówko  () is a village in the administrative district of Gmina Szczytno, within Szczytno County, Warmian-Masurian Voivodeship, in northern Poland. It lies approximately  north-west of Szczytno and  south-east of the regional capital Olsztyn.
The village has a population of 144.
